&ldquo;I have trained for 13 years for these moments, these types of games,&rdquo; Alexander-Arnold told&nbsp;The Telegraph.<br />
&ldquo;You prepare yourself for it without even knowing. I will keep working hard in the next few days to get better, to improve, to get to a new level.<br />
&ldquo;That is the main thing, to keep striving, to focus on myself and make sure I get a good game. Then there is more chance of me not giving him [Ronaldo] too many chances to do what he does best.&rdquo;

J&uuml;rgen Klopp on Emre Can: &quot;10 days ago, I didn't think it was possible he could do what he did today and in Marbella. It looked good, really positive. He's desperate to play a part.&quot;<br />
<br />
On the midfielder's future: &quot;In this moment, he's 100% #LFC and that's all I care about now&quot;
